    ]
  }
]

const realVideos = [
  [
    'Cylinder Handover, real XHand',
    'real-8x-sdr-720p/grab-s1_cylindermedium_offhand_1-xarm7_xhand-268_628_8x_sdr-720p.mp4'
  ],
  [
    'Hammer Use, real XHand',
    'real-8x-sdr-720p/grab-s1_hammer_use_1-xarm7_xhand-120_840_8x_sdr-720p.mp4'
  ],
  [
    'Cube Manipulation, real XHand',
    'real-8x-sdr-720p/grab-s2_cubemedium_inspect_1-xarm7_xhand-192_672_8x_sdr-720p.mp4'
  ]
]

const bibtex = `@misc{liang2026contrack,
      title={ConTrack: Constrained Hand Motion Tracking with Adaptive Trade-off Control}, 
      author={Liang, Yutong and Peng, Quanquan and Qiu, Ri-Zhao and Wang, Xiaolong},
      year={2026},
      eprint={xxxx.xxxxx},
      archivePrefix={arXiv},
      primaryClass={cs.RO},
      url={https://arxiv.org/abs/xxxx.xxxxx}, 
}`

const approachIntro =
  'ConTrack trains one tracking policy per clip, and the same recipe runs on all of them. It reframes what the robot has to match, controls the resulting trade-off on the fly, restarts training where the policy can actually learn, and borrows contact from the human hand to keep the motion natural.'

const approachSteps = [
  {
    title: 'Track the object, leave the hand free',
    text: 'Each clip provides a sequence of object poses to reproduce together with a human hand trajectory retargeted onto the robot. Rather than command joint angles directly, the policy outputs small residuals on top of this retargeted reference, so every action stays close to the human motion while still able to correct it for the robot’s own contact dynamics. Reproducing the object poses is the task, and matching the hand is treated as style. Since forcing the hand to match exactly is what breaks contact, ConTrack holds object tracking as a hard requirement and lets the policy give up hand fidelity whenever the two conflict.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Adapt the task-style trade-off online',
    text: 'Object tracking and hand style usually cannot both be perfect, and how hard they compete varies from clip to clip and even within one clip, so a fixed reward weighting is fragile. ConTrack instead adjusts the balance during training with a single scalar controller. A target ratio alpha sets how much tracking quality the policy must keep, measured against the best tracking it has reached so far on that clip. After each batch of rollouts the controller compares current tracking against this target: when tracking falls short it raises the weight on the object reward, and once tracking climbs back above the target it shifts weight back toward the hand. Alpha therefore controls how sensitive this update is to the object tracking reward, since a higher alpha demands closer tracking before any capacity returns to style. The same loop runs on every clip, with no per-clip reward tuning.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Reset near failures, then walk back to the start',
    text: 'Even with the trade-off handled, a clip can be long, and a policy that always restarts from the first frame keeps failing early and never reaches the later contacts to practice them. ConTrack keeps a library of restart states indexed by frame and resets training from points the policy recently failed at, so it first masters short segments near the edge of its current reach. Copying the reference state at a frame would not work here, because a hand already in contact cannot be teleported into a physically consistent pose, so the library instead stores real simulator states the policy has actually reached. As tracking on these segments improves, the reset distribution moves earlier, until training again covers the clip from the start.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Borrow contact from the human hand',
    text: 'Relaxing hand imitation and resetting from reachable states make the object easy to track, but many different robot motions can carry the object along the same path and some of them barely touch it. To pick out a natural, contact-rich solution, ConTrack reuses the contact information in the demonstration, where the reference labels which hand link touches the object and where on the object surface. The style reward encourages the same links to make contact at the same moments, and when a link and the object do touch it pulls the contact toward the labelled point. This selects the demonstrated grip out of the many that move the object equally well, without ever requiring the robot to copy the full hand pose.'
  }
]
---

<html lang='en-US'>
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title='ConTrack'
      description={description}
      canonical='/projects/ConTrack'
      ogImage={teaserImage.src}
    />
    <ThemeProvider />
  </head>
  <body class='contrack-body'>
    <main class='page'>
      <header class='hero'>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class='authors'>
          {
            authors.map((author, index) => (
              <>
                <a
                  href={author.href}
                  target={author.href === '#' ? undefined : '_blank'}
                  rel={author.href === '#' ? undefined : 'noopener noreferrer'}
                >
                  {author.name}
                </a>
                {index < authors.length - 1 && <span>, </span>}
              </>
            ))
          }
        </p>
        <p class='affiliations'>University of California San Diego</p>
        <p class='links'>
          {
            links.map((link) => (
              <a
                href={link.href}
                target={link.href === '#' ? undefined : '_blank'}
                rel={link.href === '#' ? undefined : 'noopener noreferrer'}
              >
                {link.label}
              </a>
            ))
          }
        </p>
      </header>

      <figure class='teaser'>
        <img src={teaserImage.src} alt='ConTrack overview teaser.' />
      </figure>

      <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>{overviewIntro}</p>
        <ul class='overview-list'>
          {overviewPoints.map((point) => <li>{point}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Video</h2>
        <iframe
          class='main-video'
          src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/Rr96tHf0ZUU'
          title='ConTrack video'
          allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
          allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Method</h2>
        <p>{approachIntro}</p>
        <ul class='method-steps'>
          {
            approachSteps.map((step) => (
              <li>
                <div>
                  <strong>{step.title}</strong>
                  <span>{step.text}</span>
                </div>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Experiment</h2>
        <p>
          We test ConTrack on bimanual object manipulation (GRAB), articulated tool use (ARCTIC),
          and in-hand rotation (DexterHand). Each video below is one policy per clip, trained with
          the same recipe and shown on both the XHand and Sharpa robot hands.
        </p>

        <h3>Simulation Videos</h3>
        {
          simGroups.map((group) => (
            <div class='sim-group'>
              <h4>{group.name}</h4>
              <div class='video-grid'>
                {group.videos.map(([name, src]) => (
                  <figure>
                    <video
                      class='lazy-video'
                      muted
                      loop
                      playsinline
                      autoplay
                      preload='none'
                      data-src={`${cdn}${src}`}
                    />
                    <figcaption>{name}</figcaption>
                  </figure>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }

        <h3>Real Robot Videos</h3>
        <div class='real-grid'>
          {
            realVideos.map(([name, src]) => (
              <figure>
                <video
                  class='lazy-video'
                  muted
                  loop
                  playsinline
                  autoplay
                  preload='none'
                  data-src={`${cdn}${src}`}
                />
                <figcaption>{name}</figcaption>
              </figure>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>BibTeX</h2>
        <pre><code>{bibtex}</code></pre>
      </section>
    </main>
    <script>
      const videos = [...document.querySelectorAll('video.lazy-video')] as HTMLVideoElement[]
      const loadVideo = (video: HTMLVideoElement) => {
        const src = video.dataset.src
        if (!src || video.src) return
        video.preload = 'auto'
        video.src = src
        video.load()
        video.play().catch(() => {})
      }

      const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            const video = entry.target as HTMLVideoElement
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              loadVideo(video)
              video.play().catch(() => {})
            } else {
              video.pause()
            }
          })
        },
        { rootMargin: '360px 0px', threshold: 0.08 }
      )

      videos.forEach((video) => observer.observe(video))
    </script>
    <Analytics />
    <SpeedInsights />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :global(body.contrack-body) {
    --contrack-bg: #fff;
    --contrack-text: #111;
    --contrack-muted: #555;
    --contrack-link: #1f5fae;
    --contrack-button-border: #d8d8d8;
    --contrack-button-hover: #f7f7f4;
    --contrack-button-ink: #171717;
    --contrack-line: #ddd;
    --contrack-code-bg: #f7f7f7;
    --contrack-video-bg: #000;
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--contrack-bg);
    color: var(--contrack-text);
  }

  :global(html.dark body.contrack-body) {
    --contrack-bg: #0b0b10;
    --contrack-text: #e8e8ee;
    --contrack-muted: #a6a6b3;
    --contrack-link: #8ab4ff;
    --contrack-button-border: #3a3a45;
    --contrack-button-hover: #15151c;
    --contrack-button-ink: #ededf3;
    --contrack-line: #31313a;
    --contrack-code-bg: #17171f;
  }

  .page {
    width: min(980px, calc(100% - 32px));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 0 72px;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.62;
  }

  .hero {
    text-align: center;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 18px;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .authors,
  .affiliations,
  .links {
    margin: 6px 0;
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .authors {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
  }

  .affiliations,
  .muted {
    color: var(--contrack-muted);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--contrack-link);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .links a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 36px;
    border: 1px solid var(--contrack-button-border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0 13px;
    color: var(--contrack-button-ink);
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, 'Liberation Mono',
      'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.2;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition:
      background-color 160ms ease,
      border-color 160ms ease,
      transform 160ms ease;
  }

  .links a:hover {
    background: var(--contrack-button-hover);
    border-color: var(--contrack-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .teaser {
    margin: 34px 0 46px;
  }

  .teaser img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
  }

  section {
    margin-top: 52px;
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--contrack-line);
    padding-bottom: 6px;
    font-size: 1.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  h3 {
    margin: 30px 0 10px;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  h4 {
    margin: 18px 0 10px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .overview-list {
    margin: 8px 0 0;
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .overview-list li {
    position: relative;
    margin: 8px 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .overview-list li::before {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0.72em;
    left: 0;
    width: 0.34rem;
    height: 0.34rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--contrack-text);
    content: '';
  }

  video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--contrack-video-bg);
  }

  .main-video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    border: 0;
    background: var(--contrack-video-bg);
  }

  .method-steps {
    display: grid;
    gap: 14px;
    margin: 6px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .method-steps li {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--contrack-line);
    padding-top: 14px;
  }

  .method-steps li:first-child {
    border-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .method-steps strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .method-steps span {
    display: block;
    color: var(--contrack-muted);
  }

  strong {
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .sim-group {
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .video-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .real-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .real-grid figure {
    width: calc((100% - 3 * 12px) / 4);
  }

  figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .video-grid video,
  .real-grid video {
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 5px;
    color: var(--contrack-muted);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  pre {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--contrack-code-bg);
    padding: 14px 16px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .video-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .real-grid figure {
      width: calc((100% - 12px) / 2);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .page {
      width: min(100% - 24px, 980px);
      padding-top: 32px;
    }
  }
</style>
